  <h1 class="mb-4 text-primary">🔗 Blockchain Beyond Cryptocurrency</h1>
  <p class="lead">Blockchain technology is revolutionizing various industries beyond cryptocurrency, offering secure and transparent solutions for a wide range of applications.</p>

  <h3 class="mt-5 text-success">🏢 Blockchain in Supply Chain</h3>
  <p>Blockchain is transforming supply chain management by offering real-time tracking, increasing transparency, and reducing fraud. Companies are now able to track goods from origin to delivery with enhanced security.</p>

  <h3 class="mt-4 text-info">📝 Blockchain in Smart Contracts</h3>
  <p>Smart contracts are self-executing agreements with the terms directly written into code. Blockchain ensures the security and integrity of these contracts, eliminating the need for intermediaries and speeding up transactions.</p>

  <h3 class="mt-4 text-warning">⚖️ Blockchain in Legal Systems</h3>
  <p>Legal systems are adopting blockchain for secure document management and to create immutable records of transactions, improving the efficiency and reliability of contracts, wills, and legal certifications.</p>

  <h3 class="mt-4 text-danger">🌍 Blockchain in Voting</h3>
  <p>Blockchain offers the potential for secure and transparent voting systems, eliminating fraud and ensuring the integrity of elections by allowing votes to be securely recorded and verified.</p>

  <h3 class="mt-4 text-secondary">🏥 Blockchain in Healthcare</h3>
  <p>In healthcare, blockchain is being used for secure medical records, enhancing patient privacy, and providing real-time access to critical health data for doctors, hospitals, and patients alike.</p>
